Description: 2009 G&L ASAT Classic S Serial number CLF56535 Weight is approximately 9 lbs. The maple neck is dated 11/17/09.The swamp ash body is dated 11/20/09. The beautiful gloss maple neck, maple fret board and frets are in excellent condition, free from scratches and dents. I measured the nut width as approximately 1 5/8 inch, the neck thickness at the first fret as approximately 0.855 inch and at the twelfth fret as approximately 0.982 inch. The beautiful body is in excellent shape, too. I just noticed that it looks like the body was scratched during manufacturing in 2009, below the volume and tone controls, prior to painting with a tinted gloss clear coating (I tried to capture this in one of the photos). This is not a scratch in the tinted gloss clear coating, it's beneath the coating - you can't feel it. The prior owner provided me with a second set of strap pins and screws, these are included, along with a certificate of authenticity. The neck and bridge pickups are ASAT Classic MFDs and the bridge pickup is a S-500 MFD. There's a five position pickup selector and a push-pull volume knob that enables selection of just the neck and bridge pickups simultaneously or all three pickups simultaneously. The original G&G hard shell case is in excellent condition with a few minor exterior scuffs. This guitar ships domestically, internationally or it can be picked up locally.
Title: 2009 G&L ASAT Classic S USA gloss ash body, maple neck, original hard shell case
